 | datetime", "xref": null, "params": null}, "documentation": ["This function takes a datetime object and a format code as inputs and\nreturns the date formatted in various Brazilian formats.\n\n```\nparam date\n\nThe input date as a datetime object\n\ntype date\n\ndatetime\n\nparam format_date\n\nFormat code to specify the desired date format.\nAvailable options are:\n\nsource:9: (ERROR/3) Unexpected indentation.\n\n'6' : ddmmyy\n\n'8a': ddmmyyyy\n\n'8b': dd/mm/yy\n\n'8c': dd-mm-yy\n\n'10a': dd/mm/yyyy\n\n'10b': dd-mm-yyyy\n\ntype format_date\n\nstr\n\nreturn\n\nThe date formatted in the specified Brazilian date format\n\nrtype\n\nstr\n\nprocess\n\nExtract the day and month as two-digit strings.\n\nExtract the year in two formats: 'yy' and 'yyyy'.\n\nFormat the date string based on the format code provided.\n```\n\nExample:\n: ```pycon\n  >>> from datetime import datetime\n  >>> string_format_br_date(datetime(2023, 1, 1), '8a')\n  '01012023'\n  ```\n"]}, {"name": "dataprocess.dataprocessing.add_left_zero", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "value", "type": {"name": "str | int", "xref": null, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "len_desired", "type": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "dataprocess.dataprocessing.get_day_greetings", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "message", "type": {"name": "str | None", "xref": null, "params": null}, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "dataprocess.dataprocessing.match_numeric", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "value", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []